  "prompt": "What is LG G4?",
  "response": "The LG G4 is a smartphone that was developed and manufactured by LG Electronics. It was announced in April 2015 and released shortly thereafter. The LG G4 is part of LG's G series line of flagship smartphones and was designed to compete with other high-end devices from manufacturers such as Samsung, Apple, and HTC.\n\nKey features of the LG G4 include:\n\n1. **Display**: It has a 5.5-inch Quad HD IPS Quantum display with a resolution of 2560 x 1440 pixels, which provides sharp and vibrant visuals.\n\n2. **Camera**: The rear camera is a 16-megapixel sensor with an f/1.8 aperture, laser autofocus, and optical image stabilization. The front camera is an 8-megapixel sensor designed for high-quality selfies and video calls.\n\n3. **Processor**: It is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 808 processor, which supports smooth performance and multitasking.\n\n4. **RAM and Storage**: The device typically comes with 3 GB of RAM and 32 GB of internal storage, which can be expanded via a microSD card.\n\n5. **Battery**: The LG G4 comes equipped with a removable 3000 mAh battery, which also supports fast charging.\n\n6. **Design**: The LG G4 features a curved design and was available in various finishes, including leather back options for a premium look and feel.\n\n7. **Operating System**: At launch, it ran on Android 5.1 Lollipop, with updates available to newer versions of Android.\n\nThe LG G4 was well-received for its camera performance and display quality but faced some criticism regarding issues such as stability and battery life. Nonetheless, it remains a notable device in LG's lineup of smartphones.",
